    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Distribution of Wnt signaling proteins in the mouse hippocampus\"\n- \"Puncta of Wnt3a and Frizzled-4 signals showed extensive co-localizations with PSD-95 (Fig. 1, b-d and f-h), indicating their localization at the synaptic regions. As Frizzled-4 physically interacts with PSD-95 (39), this Wnt receptor is most likely localized on the post-synaptic membrane. Dishevelled-3 puncta overlapped with PSD-95 to a lesser extent (Fig. 1, j-l), whereas β-catenin displayed a more diffused pattern with signal clusters (Fig. 1, n-p), which is consistent with previous studies (40). These results suggest that Wnt signaling operates at hippocampal synapses.\". Experimental description: - \"Hippocampal slices (400 μm) were prepared from 3-4-week mice...\"\n- Species of recombinant Wnt3a used in Fig.5 is not stated in the paper.",
